      • listFolderGetLatestCursor

        public Files.ListFolderGetLatestCursorResult listFolderGetLatestCursor(java.lang.String path)
                                                                throws Files.ListFolderGetLatestCursorException,
                                                                       DbxException
        A way to quickly get a cursor for the folder's state. Unlike listFolder(com.dropbox.core.v2.Files.ListFolderArg), listFolderGetLatestCursor(com.dropbox.core.v2.Files.ListFolderArg) doesn't return any entries. This endpoint is for app which only needs to know about new files and modifications and doesn't need to know about files that already exist in Dropbox.
        Throws:
        Files.ListFolderGetLatestCursorException
        DbxException

      • createFolder

        public Files.FolderMetadata createFolder(java.lang.String path)
                                  throws Files.CreateFolderException,
                                         DbxException
        Create a folder at a given path. No file or folder may exist at the path. The parent folder will be created if it does not already exist (and so on). If the parent exists it must be a folder (and the same for any ancestor). If an ancestor is a shared folder it must have write access.
        Throws:
        Files.CreateFolderException
        DbxException
